               "id": "exercise_v2",
               "text": [
                  {
                     "question": "The steps to make a planet are: planets lose mass by gravitational forces making a protoplanet that are disintegrated into planetesimals, finally it is transformed into dust grain?",
                     "yesNoAnswer": "No",
                     "additionalInfo": "The question describes the inverse process. Remember that in nature, structures always build from the smallest to the largest."
                  },
                  {
                     "question": "When a pure substance is broken, can we still identify the molecules because they keep chemical properties?",
                     "yesNoAnswer": "Yes",
                     "additionalInfo": "Molecules are made up of smaller identical entities. For example, when water molecules are separated, we still expect to have water."
                  },
                  {
                     "question": "Do we have the life, living beings, in a planet only with specific conditions?",
                     "yesNoAnswer": "Yes",
                     "additionalInfo": "Not all planets can support life as we know it; this can be observed in our own solar system."
                  }
               ]
            },
